The Federal Medical Centre,(FMC) Owerri , Imo State has confirmed that the index case of Coronavirus recorded in the State was actually brought to their centre, on showing signs of being infected with the virus. Confirming the case to LEADERSHIP  in Owerri, the Public Relations Officer (PRO) of FMC, Owerri, Mrs Jacynta Achonu explained that the patient was brought to their facility at about 2 30 pm on Saturday for medical attention. According to her the unidentified male patient, about 45 years of age was taken straight to their isolation centre where a team of medical experts were already waiting for necessary medical blood extraction and sampling for onward transmission to the testing centre. However, she said she does not know where the patient was brought from, but stressed that the patient showed the symptoms of the virus, just as she could not confirm if the patient tested positive for the virus. “I don’t know if he was tested or not, but what I can say is that we are aware of the case, we have been waiting patiently for them until about some minutes past two when they arrived and headed straight to the isolation centre. “I can’t say for sure where they brought him from but there is no cause for alarm, the situation is under control as we have professionals that are capable to do the index case.”